Instructions for Revising Take Home Midterm Exam

1. Be mindful of feedback in the .pdf file returned to you.
    Major issues included using outside sources, organization, an arguable thesis, or playing it too safe. 
2. Turn in the revised exam no later than 7:00pm on April 29. Email the revised file to Kim.
3. Your grade may increase no more than 1 full letter grade. Your grade will not decrease
Organization
If you have comment “organization issues”- utilize a reverse outline –take each paragraph with the topic sentence to see what argument your building



1. Thesis statements:
        A thesis is always an argument. It also serves as a roadmap for the whole paper. Thesis statements can
        have multiple subpoints. In the paper, these should be organized as indicated in the introduction. Thesis 
        statements should be in the introduction paragraph. They should be explicit and succinct.

    + Roadmap = argument -> that is required factor
    + eg: dog & cat -> how to begin this argue
2. Using Sources
- paraphrase when possible
    + sounds like you
    + integrated quote
    + in most cases
    + emphsize
- contextualize
- analyze

3. Organization
- Global organization
    + thesis
    + follow roadmap laid out by thesis and intro paragraph

- Paragraph organization
    + one subject / topic each
    + topic sentence
    + evidence
    + transitions in between
    + reverse outline
- just only 1 topic
- transitions 
    + eg: last sentence of paragraph or the beginning sentence of the paragraph
    + words as the signal eg: moreover, furthermore etc.
- outline topic sentence
- reverse outline
    +First sentence- Topic sentence
    +Evidence- building an argument
    +Transitions 
    +Flow from paragraph to paragraph and building an argument
    +Specific evidence
